news: EU leaders agree on a 200bn euro stimulus plan to help boost European growth following the global financial crisis.
Greece is burdened with debt amounting to 113% of GDP — nearly double the eurozone limit of 60%. Ratings agencies start to downgrade Greek bank and government debt.
EU orders France, Spain, Ireland and Greece to reduce their budget deficits.
An EU report condemns "severe irregularities" in Greek accounting procedures.
The EU and IMF agree to a bailout package to the Irish Republic totalling 85bn euro.
Greece unveils a series of austerity measures aimed at curbing the deficit.
The Eurozone and IMF agree a safety net of 22bn euro to help Greece.
The Eurozone countries agree to provide up to 30bn euro in emergency loans.
The Eurozone members and the IMF agree a 110bn euro bailout package to rescue Greece.
Eurozone finance ministers set up a permanent bailout fund, called the European Stability Mechanism, worth about 500bn euro.
Portugal admits it cannot deal with its finances itself and asks the EU for help.
The Eurozone and the IMF approve a 78bn euro bailout for Portugal.
The Eurozone agrees a comprehensive 109bn euro package designed to resolve the Greek crisis and prevent contagion among other European economies.
The European Central Bank says it will buy Italian and Spanish government bonds to try to bring down their borrowing costs.
